### Description of Issue/Question

I cannot use complex targeting to match a grain value with a space in it.  I've tried escaping spaces, double encapsulating quotes, etc.

i.e. is not possible to do this:

`salt -C 'G@lsb_distrib_id:Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server' test.ping --log-level=all`

Although it is possible to do this:

`salt -G 'lsb_distrib_id:Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server' test.ping`
### Setup

N/A
### Steps to Reproduce Issue

See command examples above.
